Sentencas: Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+delta (PB0.5-xSCO, x = 0, 0.04 and 0.08) perovskites are synthesized.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of Ba deficiency on the phase structure, thermal expansion, electrical and electrochemical characteristics of PB0.5-xSCO are investigated.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PB0.5-xSCO samples are chemically compatible with LSGM electrolyte at 1000 degrees C. Slightly decrement of TECs with the rise of Ba deficiency content in PB0.5-xSCO is observed.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introduction of Ba deficiency promotes the formation of additional oxygen vacancies, which is responsible for the decrement of electrical conductivity and improvement of electrochemical performance of PB0.5-xSCO samples.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity is higher than 580 Scm(-1) for PB0.5-xSCO perovskites within 50-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance is promoted significantly by introducing Ba deficiency in PB0.5-xSCO.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ASRs of the Ba-deficient PB0.5-xSCO decreased by more than 60% in comparison with the sample without Badeficiency, indicating the introduction of Ba deficiency is an effective way to improve the electrochemical characteristic of PB0.5-xSCO cathodes.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site Ba-deficient PrBa0.5-xSr0.5Co2O5+δ (x=0, 0.04 and 0.08) as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
